Quote: He [a sheep dog] wasn't particularly good at running out and he was a bit slack at hand - he was too kind and sheep had no fear of him whatever. <i>Ibid.</i> 169 (Glossary) <i>Slack</i>: A slack dog - mainly applicable to heading dogs - is one which is slow to pull or generally ineffective in its work.
